The `cdata.ptr()` method returns a pointer to the cdata. The `cdata.deref()` method
dereferences a pointer to read the value.

Pointer and dereference basic usage.

-- Testcase --
{%
import * as ffi from 'ffi';

let i = ffi.ctype('int', 42);
let p = i.ptr();

let addr = p.get();
print("address is valid: ", addr != null && addr > 0, "\n");
print("value: ", p.deref('int'), "\n");
-- End --

-- Expect stdout --
address is valid: true
value: 42
-- End --


Dereference returns primitive value directly.

-- Testcase --
{%
import * as ffi from 'ffi';

let i = ffi.ctype('int', 123);
let p = i.ptr();
let v = p.deref('int');

print("type of deref: ", type(v), "\n");
print("value: ", v, "\n");
-- End --

-- Expect stdout --
type of deref: int
value: 123
-- End --

